5 b. A law enforcement officer may:
6 (1) Investigate possible delinquent offenses and conduct occurring at a school,
7 including conducting probable cause searches;
8 (2) Consult with school staff about the conduct of a child enrolled in a school;
9 (3) Refer a child to the juvenile court for a delinquent offense occurring on
10 school grounds or on school property as allowed by this section;
11 (4) Transport a child enrolled in a school to a location permitted by law;
12 (5) Take temporary custody of a child in accordance with section 27-20.4-05 or
13 protective custody of a child in accordance with section 27-20.3-06; and
14 (6) Protect the safety of students and the school community.
